        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 2:00PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers near Linn,
moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Linn, Encino, San Manuel, Rachal, and El Coyote Ranch Airport.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 732 and 760.

In addition to the gusty winds, brief downpours will reduce
visibiity below 1 mile on farm to market and county roads, and
possibly below one-half mile along US 281 in Brooks County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
